 {"id":"franken_numpy-jkuy","title":"Implement integer overflow wrapping for same-type integer arithmetic","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-04-07T03:23:37.936330495Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-07T03:35:49.155108255Z","closed_at":"2026-04-07T03:35:49.154738484Z","close_reason":"Fixed: changed ArrayStorage::set_f64 to use NumPy-compatible wrapping via i128 intermediary instead of Rust's saturating float-to-int casts. All 3 overflow test cases now pass (U8 255+1→0, I8 127+1→-128, I64 2^63 wraps). Zero regressions across 2878 tests.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["dtype","parity"],"comments":[{"id":26,"issue_id":"franken_numpy-jkuy","author":"ubuntu","text":"NumPy wraps on integer overflow for same-type ops (U8 255+1=0, I8 127+1=-128, I64 2^63 wraps). FrankenNumPy computes via f64 so no wrapping occurs. Discovered during br-x6kc cross-dtype testing.","created_at":"2026-04-07T03:24:12Z"}]}
